   SIGPLAN

Special Interest Group on Programming Languages

   The ACM Special Interest Group on Programming Languages (SIGPLAN)
   explores programming language concepts and tools, focusing on design,
   implementation, practice, and theory. Its members are programming
   language developers, educators, implementers, researchers,
   theoreticians, and users.

