Awards and Recent Recipients

Programming Languages Achievement Award (presented in 2019)

     * Alex Aiken

Distinguished Service Award (presented in 2018)

     * Zena Ariola

Programming Languages Software Award (presented in 2019)

     * Scala

Robin Milner Young Researcher Award (presented in 2019)

     * Martin Vechev

John C. Reynolds Doctoral Dissertation Award (presented in 2019)

     * Ryan Beckett, Princeton University
       Network Control Plane Synthesis and Verification

Most Influential POPL Paper Award (presented in 2019)

     * Cristiano Calcagno, Dino Distefano, Peter W. O'Hearn, Hongseok Yang
       (for 2009): Compositional shape analysis by means of bi-abduction

Most Influential PLDI Paper Award (presented in 2019)

     * Cormac Flanagan (UC Santa Cruz) and Stephen N. Freund (Williams
       College)
       (for 2009) FastTrack: Efficient and Precise Dynamic Race Detection

Most Influential ICFP Paper Award (presented in 2019)

     * Simon Marlow, Simon Peyton Jones, and Satnam Singh
       (for 2009) Runtime Support for Multicore Haskell

Most Influential OOPSLA Paper Award (presented in 2018)

     * Dino Distefano, Matthew Parkinson
       (for 2008) jStar: towards practical verification for Java

Other Awards at SIGPLAN-sponsored Events (presented in 2019)

     * ASPLOS Most Influential Paper Award: Emery D. Berger, Kathryn S.
       McKinley, Robert D. Blumofe, and Paul R. Wilson
       Hoard: A Scalable Memory Allocator for Multithreaded Applications

ACM Fellows (recognized in 2017)

     * Lars Birkedal, Gail C. Murphy, and Aarti Gupta

